                  <decoDesc>
                     <summary>On the E face there are three supposedly classical figures, one at each corner and one in the middle. The one in the SW corner is of a man holding a scroll with a bird, presumably a dove, at his feet. The man may be Christ. The middle one shows a male figure standing on a sheep and holding a lyre and a possible paint brush. He is next to a tree with a dove(?) in it. He could be Apollo. The one in the NE corner shows a man holding a possible scroll.</summary>
